header.gameNote: FRANKLIN AMERICAN MORTGAGE MUSIC CITY BOWL

videos.description: Nebraska head coach Mike Riley talks about playing without starting QB Tommy Armstrong Jr.
videos.headline: Nebraska coach Mike Riley on playing without starting QB

videos.description: Tennessee's Joshua Dobbs connects with Josh Malone for 31-yards.
videos.headline: Dobbs finds Malone for 31-yard gain

videos.description: Tennessee's John Kelly runs for a 28-yard touchdown, getting the Volunteers on the board first in the Music City Bowl.
videos.headline: Tennessee gets on the board with long TD run

videos.description: Tennessee's Joshua Dobbs keeps it and runs 10-yards into the end zone, extending the Volunteers lead 14-0.
videos.headline: Dobbs keeps it to extend Tennessee lead

videos.description: Nebraska's Ryker Fyfe hurls it to Brandon Reilly, who makes the diving catch for a 38-yard touchdown.
videos.headline: Nebraska scores off impressive diving TD

videos.description: Tennessee's Joshua Dobbs runs it into the end zone for two yards for his second rushing touchdown of the game.
videos.headline: Dobbs runs it into the end zone for the second time

videos.description: Tennessee head coach Butch Jones talks about QB Joshua Dobbs first-half performance against Nebraska.
videos.headline: Tennessee coach Butch Jones talks about Dobbs

videos.description: Nebraska's De'Mornay Pierson-El fumbles the ball, forced out by Tennessee's Malik Foreman, who recovers the ball for the Volunteers.
videos.headline: Tennessee forces fumble on Nebraska's opening drive of second half

videos.description: Nebraska's Ryker Fyfe passes to Brandon Reilly who makes the fantastic catch for the 9-yard touchdown.
videos.headline: Nebraska's Reilly makes another highlight TD catch

videos.description: Tennessee's Joshua Dobbs runs into the end zone for the 3-yard touchdown, extending the Volunteers lead 31-14.
videos.headline: Dobbs pads Tennessee's lead with third rushing TD

videos.description: Nebraska's Ryker Fyfe hurls it up for Brandon Reilly who climbs the ladder to make another incredible catch for 39 yards.
videos.headline: Nebraska's Reilly continues highlight reel game

videos.description: After kicking a field goal, Nebraska's JoJo Domann forces the fumble on the kickoff, with the ball being recovered by Mohamed Barry for the Cornhuskers.
videos.headline: Nebraska forces a fumble on kickoff

videos.description: Nebraska's Ryker Fyfe fakes the handoff and rushes nine yards for a touchdown in inch the Cornhuskers closer to Tennessee in the fourth quarter.
videos.headline: Nebraska's Fyfe runs the draw to the end zone

videos.description: Tennessee's Joshua Dobbs hurls it downfield to Josh Malone for the 59-yard catch for a touchdown.
videos.headline: Dobbs airs it deep for the 59-yard TD in Vols' win

videos.description: Tennessee's Derek Barnett sets school record with 33rd career sack, passing Reggie White, in the fourth quarter against Nebraska.
videos.headline: Barnett passes Reggie White for Tennessee sack record in win

videos.description: Tennessee hoists the Franklin American Mortgage Music City Bowl trophy after their win over Nebraska.
videos.headline: Tennessee lifts the Music City Bowl trophy

videos.description: Tennessee head coach Butch Jones dedicates Franklin American Mortgage Music City Bowl victory to strong senior class.
videos.headline: Tennessee coach Butch Jones dedicates win to senior class

videos.description: Tennessee QB Joshua Dobbs is presented with the Franklin American Mortgage Music City Bowl MVP trophy.
videos.headline: Tennessee's Dobbs is presented with Music City Bowl MVP

videos.description: Tennessee QB Joshua Dobbs talks about his final game as a Volunteer and his legacy at the program.
videos.headline: Tennessee QB Joshua Dobbs on his legacy as a Volunteer

videos.description: Andre Ware and Tom Hart break down Tennessee's Joshua Dobbs and Derek Barnett's performance in the Franklin American Mortgage Music City Bowl.
videos.headline: Breaking down Dobbs and Barnett's performance in the Music City Bowl
